  1→//! Write operations (copy, move, delete) with streaming progress.
  2→//!
  3→//! All operations run in background tasks and emit progress events at configurable intervals.
  4→//! Operations support batch processing (multiple source files) and cancellation.
  5→//!
  6→//! Safety features:
  7→//! - Path canonicalization to prevent ".." and symlink bypass of recursion checks
  8→//! - Destination writability check before starting
  9→//! - Pre-flight disk space validation after scan
 10→//! - Inode identity check to prevent copy-over-self via symlinks/hard links
 11→//! - Path/name length validation (255-byte name, 1024-byte path)
 12→//! - Special file filtering (skips sockets, FIFOs, devices)
 13→//! - macOS copyfile(3) for full metadata preservation (xattrs, ACLs, resource forks)
 14→//! - Symlink preservation (not dereferenced)
 15→//! - Symlink loop detection to prevent infinite recursion
 16→//! - Copy rollback on failure (CopyTransaction)
 17→//! - Atomic cross-filesystem moves using staging directory
